The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted dry and dusty atmosphere over the northern region with slight moisture build up across the southern region. NiMet’s weather outlook released on Friday in Abuja predicted dust haze condition with horizontal visibility of 2 to 5km over the northern states within the forecast period. The agency further predicted day and night temperatures of the region to be 28 to 34 degree Celsius and 9 to 22 degree Celsius. “For central states, dust haze condition with horizontal visibility of 2 to 5km is anticipated over the region with day and night temperatures to be 28 to 37 degree Celsius and 11 to 23 degree Celsius. “For southern states, early morning mist/fog are probable over the coastal citities while hazy and partly cloudy condition is to prevail over the region within the forecast period. “Day and night temperatures of the region are expected to be 31 to 37 and 19 to 26, respectively,” it said. (NAN) 